definition: (before a noun) Do (you, they etc) have ...?/Is there a ...?/(before a verb) Did (you, they etc) (verb, infinitive)?/Have (you, they etc) (verb, past participle)?
to have/there is/there are/to exist/to be
to have/there is/there are/to exist/to be

sentences.english: Okay. Do you have our fax number?
sentences.chinese: 好的。你有沒有我們的傳真號碼呢？

sentences.english: Are there any points of resistance to this process of shifting people’s mindsets?
sentences.chinese: 有沒有對改變人們心態進程表示反對的意見呢？

sentences.english: Did anyone find a small canvas bag ?
sentences.chinese: 有沒有人撿到一個攝影包？

sentences.english: Is there any way I can improve my memory?
sentences.chinese: 有沒有什麼方法可以改善我的記憶力？

sentences.english: Han Jia, are there more buns that we should try?
sentences.chinese: 韓佳，有沒有我們沒有嘗過的包子？

sentences.english: Is there something she leaves out that you would put in?
sentences.chinese: 有沒有她遺漏的證據是你當算提出的？

sentences.english: Is here a bus stop near by?
sentences.chinese: 我想問問附近有沒有公車站？

sentences.english: Will it receive heartfelt support from the people concerned?
sentences.chinese: 有沒有得到有關人羣發自內心的擁護？

sentences.english: Did you tell Mr. Duvall who else did it?
sentences.chinese: 有沒有告訴杜瓦爾先生還有誰？

sentences.english: Have you been tapped for any other voice roles this season or next?
sentences.chinese: 你有沒有爲這一季或下一季的其他角色配過音？
他有沒有“強大的”進攻性網絡武器？

sentences.english: Do men and women eat differently for comfort?
sentences.chinese: 在喫的方面，男女有沒有不同的趨好？

sentences.english: A: Yes, do you have any particular buildings in Kowloon Bay in mind?
sentences.chinese: 可以，在九龍灣你有沒有特別指定的工業大廈？

sentences.english: The female cub is waiting aside and see if her brothers have made any progress.
sentences.chinese: 小雌虎則在一旁等待哥哥們有沒有進展。
